```rust
fn max_element<T: PartialOrd>(slice: &[T]) -> Option<&T> {
    if slice.is_empty() {
        return None;
    }
    let mut max = &slice[0];
    for item in slice.iter() {
        if item > max {
            max = item;
        }
    }
    Some(max)
}

fn main() {
    let numbers = [7, 3, 10, 5, 2];
    match max_element(&numbers) {
        Some(max) => println!("Max element is {}", max),
        None => println!("Slice is empty"),
    }
}
```

### How it works:
- Uses generics and `PartialOrd` so it works for all types that can be compared.
- Returns `Option<&T>` so it handles empty slices gracefully.
