```rust
fn is_prime(n: u64) -> bool {
    if n <= 1 {
        return false;
    }
    if n == 2 || n == 3 {
        return true;
    }
    if n % 2 == 0 || n % 3 == 0 {
        return false;
    }
    let mut i = 5;
    while i * i <= n {
        if n % i == 0 || n % (i + 2) == 0 {
            return false;
        }
        i += 6;
    }
    true
}

fn main() {
    for n in 0..20 {
        println!("{} is prime? {}", n, is_prime(n));
    }
}
```

**How it works:**
- Handles numbers less than or equal to 1 (not prime).
- Handles 2 and 3 (prime).
- Removes multiples of 2 and 3 immediately.
- Checks divisibility for numbers up to √n using the 6k ± 1 optimization.

